  "summary": "crashing",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "i opined minecraft but fore some reason it was stuck on the loading screen and the only way that i could fix this is restart my pc ore alt F4 n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Launch Minecraft on your device.\n2. Wait for the game to load until you see the splash screen.\n3. Observe the game as it attempts to progress past the loading screen.\n4. Remain on the loading screen for a minimum of 2 minutes without any progress.\n5. Attempt to exit the game by pressing Alt + F4.\n6. If the game does not respond, restart your computer.\n7. After restarting, relaunch Minecraft and observe if the issue persists.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Version 1.21.8",
  "Observed Behavior": "When launching Minecraft, the game becomes unresponsive and remains stuck on the loading screen indefinitely. This issue prevents the player from accessing the main menu or any gameplay features. The only solutions available to resolve this issue are to either forcefully close the game using the Alt + F4 keyboard shortcut or to restart the entire PC. This problem has been consistently reproducible and occurs every time the game is launched under certain conditions, which may include specific system configurations or recent updates. It is important to note that this issue does not produce an error report or crash log, making it challenging to diagnose the underlying cause. The game appears to be attempting to load resources or connect to online services but fails to progress beyond the initial loading phase.",
  "Expected Behavior": "When launching Minecraft, the game should successfully transition from the loading screen to the main menu without freezing or crashing. Players should be able to access their worlds, settings, and other features without the need to restart their computer or forcefully close the application. If there are connectivity issues or resource limitations, appropriate error messages should be displayed, guiding the player on how to resolve the issue without experiencing a complete halt in gameplay. The game should handle loading processes efficiently, ensuring a smooth experience consistent with the intended functionality of the software.",
